# Bench comparison (bench/BENCH.md): what does the assembly module add over
# the raw Boss-desk idea? A = the one-line idea as-is; B = the same idea run
# through the planner port. The diff IS the module's contribution: stages,
# owned paths, gates from world/hermes/gates/, test profile, race stage.
BASE_CMD='cat world/assembly/example/idea.txt'
NEW_CMD='python3 world/assembly/assembly.py plan "$(cat world/assembly/example/idea.txt)"'
NOTE='assembly port: one-line idea vs structured gated plan (deterministic, so diff should stay stable across cycles)'
